                <head>No. 412.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hunter</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Biddle</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of. State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1872-08-07">
                            <hi rend="italic">August</hi> 7, 1872</date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 26.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Referring to your dispatch, No. 61, of the 29th
                    of June last, transmitting correspondence with the government of Salvador upon
                    the subject of the neutrality of the interoceanic railway of Honduras, I have to
                    inform you that the position which you have taken in regard to the matter is
                    approved.</p>
                <p>I am, &amp;c.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>W. HUNTER,<lb/>
                        <hi rend="italic">Acting Secretary.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
